<div class="subSectionTitle">Section III: Haulers</div>

<div class="subSectionDesc">WIP<div style="clear: both"></div></div>


<div class="subSectionTitle">Section IV: Explorers</div>

<div class="subSectionDesc">Explorers are known for having a very... interesting body design. They are usually seen with Domed cockpits but are also seen with corner glass, which will be shown. Unlike fighters, there are only about 2 diferent types of explorers.<div style="clear: both"></div></div>

<img src="https://steamuserimages-a.akamaihd.net/ugc/913533862982407120/2FCA37ED1A9EFFE22429ABDC2A610209A7A95D96/" class="responsive">
<div class="subSectionDesc">WIP<div style="clear: both"></div></div>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<div class="subSectionTitle">Section V: Exotics</div>

<div class="subSectionDesc">Ahh, the finer things in life. Living in excess, just like the 80's. Exotic ships are rare and unique, falling under the S-Class tier of ship. They have high WarpDrive Boosts, but less Damage/Shield than other S-Class ships. You could consider these like “Grand Touring” luxury cars. <div style="clear: both"></div></div>
<br>
<br>
<img src="https://steamuserimages-a.akamaihd.net/ugc/979981833838245010/21694658F25986EAC082098B0B0A6E3D2DA644EA/" class="responsive">
<div class="subSectionDesc"> "Royal Ships"- These are always known for the Regal trim around the Sphere shaped cockpit. They have an average of about 14-16 useable Storage Slots, and around 5 Technology slots. These are great for  showing off to your friends about how lucky you are, but not exactly much else. These ships are always fetching a pretty penny, while being priced around $9,000,000-$11,000,000<div style="clear: both"></div></div>
<br>
<img src="https://steamuserimages-a.akamaihd.net/ugc/979981833838245631/BE650D51C7B4149EE1CC1AAFDB431F1152DF72A4/" class="responsive">
<div class="subSectionDesc"> "Space Squids"- Talk about design... Not many people know these S-Class ships. A bit more pricey and a lot more rare. Unlike the last ship, this exotic can show off some worth for its exorbitant price. HyperDrive being on the top along side maneuverability allows these ships to easily navigate through obstacles. They can be equipped fairly for one with an average of 15-17 useable Storage Slots and 6 Tech slots. These don’t come cheap and will cost about $13,000,000.<div style="clear: both"></div></div>

